{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox video game | title = Anno Online | image = Anno Online.jpg | caption = | developer = [[Blue Byte]] | publisher = [[Ubisoft]] | designer = | engine = | series = ''[[Anno (series)|Anno]]'' | platforms = [[Browser game|Browser]] | released = 19 March 2013 | genre = Strategy | modes = [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]] |alt = }} '''''Anno Online''''' was a [[free-to-play]] strategy [[browser game]] by Ubisoft. It was a spinoff of the [[Anno (series)|''Anno'' series]]. Players developed and managed island braced cites from the first settlers to commercial empires.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anno Online|url=https://www.ubisoft.com/en-GB/game/anno-online/|website=Ubisoft|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref>
English closed beta started on 23 April 2013, and open beta started on 14 May 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Free-To-Play Anno Online Enters Open Beta Today|url=http://gameslatestnews.com/2013/05/14/free-to-play-anno-online-enters-open-beta-today-1961/|work=GamesLatestNews|accessdate=14 May 2013}}</ref> Beta status ended on 25 September 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=News Archive|url=http://en.anno-online.com/en-GB/news-archive?page=12|website=Anno Online|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref> The game was in "maintenance mode" starting Sept 2017, meaning there was no further development or major in-game events. The game was closed on 31 January 2018.
