{{For|other persons|Kate Long (disambiguation)|}}
'''Kate Long''' is an [[United States|American]] [[songwriter]] and [[storytelling|storyteller]] who writes songs that have been recorded by dozens of artists and won national awards, including the [[International Bluegrass Music Association]] Song of the Year. She is the writing coach for [[The Charleston Gazette]] and produces for [[West Virginia Public Broadcasting]]. She hosted and produced the national award-winning ''In Their Own Country'' public radio series. She regularly performs at [[storytelling festival]]s around the country.
She is currently co-director and founder of Try This West Virginia.<ref>[https://www.linkedin.com/in/kate-long-142bb35/ LinkedIn profile for Kate Long]</ref><ref>[http://www.TryThisWV.com Try This West Virginia website]</ref><ref>[https://encore.org/purpose-prize/kate-long/ Encore.org Prize Announcement of Kate Long as Purpose Prize Fellow 2015]</ref>
==See also== *[[Storytelling]] *[[Storytelling festival]]
