{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}
<!-- EDIT BELOW THIS LINE --> {{Infobox software | name = Magister | screenshot = | screenshot alt = Magister logo | developer = Schoolmaster | latest release version = 6.1.15<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://amsterdams.magister.net/|title=Het Amsterdams Lyceum}}</ref> | latest release date = August 2017 | operating system = [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Mac OS X]], [[Linux]] (not since August 2014), [[Symbian]], [[iOS (Apple)|iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] | genre = [[Web application]], [[Mobile application|app]] | license = Commercial | website ={{url|schoolmaster.nl}} }} '''Magister''' is a Dutch online administrative application, used in the [[Education in the Netherlands|schooling system]] in secondary education. All of the students' information is on this platform. Students, parents and teachers are able to access this at all times. It is used to keep up with the management, administration and health issues of students, and users can also view their grades, timetable, homework assignments and absences. In 2012 the software had a 70% market share in the Netherlands.<ref name="webwereld.nl">[http://webwereld.nl/overheid/56466-scholieren-afgesloten-van-gesloten-schoolsoftware webwereld.nl] published on 2 October 2013</ref>
Magister was put on the market as a [[SaaS]] (software as a service) by the company Schoolmaster, located in [[Leeuwarden]]. The company has been a part of the Iddink-groep since 2009.<ref>http://www.schoolmaster.nl/Home/Bedrijf.aspx</ref>
== Access == There are different ways to access Magister.
=== Computer === To be able to access Magister, installation of [[Microsoft Silverlight|Silverlight]] is needed. Since August 2014, this caused people to have issues, using the computer version that used [[Linux]] as an [[operating system]].{{clarification needed|date=June 2018}}{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}
=== Mobile phone === There is an [[mobile app]] for [[iOS (Apple)|iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] (''Meta''). On this app, students can see their grades and timetables, and message their teacher and other students.<ref name="webwereld.nl"></ref>
==Magister 6== [[File:Magister, Het Amsterdams Lyceum.jpg|thumb|Magister 6 screenshot]] Magister 6, the latest version of the program, was published in August of 2014.<ref>[http://www.magister6.nl Magister 6]</ref> It is available for students, teachers and parents.
After its launch, several groups tried integrating the technology in other ways.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://github.com/DutchCodeGeeks/MagisterHub/blob/master/libs/Magister6.md |title= MagisterHub Libraries |accessdate= 1 May 2016 |language= en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url= https://github.com/DutchCodeGeeks/MagisterHub/blob/master/apps/Magister6.md |title= MagisterHub Apps |accessdate= 1 May 2016 |language= en}}</ref> This was possible, because the new version offers support to [[Representational state transfer|REST]]-[[Application programming interface|api]], which made the process of storing information easier.
