{{Refimprove|date=January 2010}}
'''Meltdown''' is an annual festival held in London, featuring a mix of music, art, performance and film. Meltdown is held in June at [[Southbank Centre]], the arts complex covering {{convert|21|acre|m2}} and including the [[Royal Festival Hall]], the [[Queen Elizabeth Hall]] and [[Hayward Gallery|The Hayward]]. Each year the festival chooses an established music artist or act as director of the event and they pick the performers of their choosing. Previous Meltdown directors have included [[Elvis Costello]], [[David Bowie]], [[Patti Smith]], [[Lee "Scratch" Perry|Lee Scratch Perry]], [[Morrissey]], [[Jarvis Cocker]], [[Nick Cave]], [[Scott Walker (singer)|Scott Walker]], [[John Peel]] and [[Ornette Coleman]]. The festival has been held annually since 1993, except in 2006 when the Royal Festival Hall was closed for refurbishment. In 2018, [[Robert Smith (musician)|Robert Smith]], lead singer of [[The Cure]], curated the 25th Meltdown.
