id Taha]], [[Richard Hell]], [[Roy Harper (singer)|Roy Harper]], [[Sinéad O'Connor]], [[Steve Earle]], [[Television (band)|Television]], [[Tinariwen]], [[Tori Amos]], [[Yat-Kha]], [[Yoko Ono]] |- | 2006 | N/A | Royal Festival Hall closed for refurbishment |- | 2007 | [[Jarvis Cocker]] | [[Cornershop]], [[Iggy & The Stooges]], [[The Jesus and Mary Chain]], [[Motörhead]], [[Devo]], [[Melanie Safka]], [[Roky Erickson]], [[Sunn O)))]], [[Littl'ans]], [[Scout Niblett]], [[Selfish Cunt]], [[KPM Musichouse|KPM Allstars]], [[John Barry (composer)|John Barry]], [[The Valerie Project]], [[1990s (band)|1990s]], [[Mathew Sawyer|Mathew Sawyer and The Ghosts]], [[Clinic (band)|Clinic]] |- | 2008 | [[Massive Attack]] | [[Massive Attack]], [[Gong (band)|Gong]], [[Yellow Magic Orchestra]], [[Reggae Acoustic Songbook]], [[Princess Malachi]], [[Elbow (band)|Elbow]], [[Fleet Foxes]], [[The Heritage Orchestra: Music from Blade Runner]], [[Stiff Little Fingers]], [[Mark Stewart (musician)|Mark Stewart]], [[The Maffia]], [[Adrian Sherwood]], [[The Shortwave Set]], [[Martina Topley]], [[Grace Jones]], [[Dälek]], [[The Cool Kids]], [[Shape Of Broad Minds]], [[Flying Lotus]], [[Gang Of Four (band)|Gang Of Four]], [[Tom Tom Club]], [[Terry Callier]], [[Aloe Blacc]], [[Tunng]], [[Leila Arab|Leila]], [[Saxon Studio International|Saxon Sound System]] with [[Musclehead]], [[Tippa Irie]], [[Trevor Sax]] and [[Papa Levi]], [[Silent Disco]] with guests DJs including [[Four Tet]] and [[Peaches (musician)|Peaches]] |- | 2009 | [[Ornette Coleman]] | [[The Roots]], [[David Murray (saxophonist)|David Murray]] with the [[Gwo-Ka Masters]] and [[Jamaaladeen Tacuma]], [[Yoko Ono]] and the [[Plastic Ono Band]] with [[Sean Lennon]] and [[Cornelius (musician)|Cornelius]], [[Baaba Maal]], [[Yo La Tengo]], [[Moby]], [[Bobby McFerrin]], [[Patti Smith]] and [[The Silver Mt. Zion Memorial Orchestra & Tra-La-La Band]], [[Master Musicians of Jajouka]], [[Charlie Haden]] and the [[Liberation Music Orchestra]] with [[Ca