{{Theat-stub}}

{{multiple issues| {{Orphan|date=April 2011}} {{unreferenced|date=June 2013}} }}
{{Infobox sport | image= | imagesize= | caption= | union= | nickname= Vettu Panthu | first= | first team= | registered= | clubs= Local teams at Kottayam | contact=Kerala Native ball Association 9497720791. | team=7 players per side | mgender= male | category=[[ball games]] | ball=leather ball filled with cotton | olympic= }}
A popular sports played in villages of [[Kottayam]] district and Muvattupuzha Taluk. Villages like Manaracd, [[Puthuppally, Kottayam|Puthuppally]], Thottakkadu, Thirvanchoor, Meendam, Manganam, Kurichy, Valakom, Pampady etc. are the places where this game is played. The popularity of game is dying as there is not much money and younger generation are more interested in cricket.
This game is played using small ball made of leather and filled with cotton or coconut fibre. Each team consist of 5 or 7 players each. The game is played for 5 Innings (vara). Each inning, both the teams are allowed to do "vettu" where they initiate the scoring and other team prevents from the scoring. Scoring points follow the sequence like otta, petta, pidiyan, thalm, Keezhu, Indan and then it repeats. the team which score the most points from the innings wins.
Annual Tournaments are conducted at these villages every year and there is lot people supporting the local teams.
